Description: Alexey Tolstoy (1817-1875) - a classic of Russian literature.
Range of genres in which he wrote , AK Tolstoy is unusually wide : from bright satire ( " Kozma bars " ) to deep tragedy ( "The Death of Ivan the Terrible ", etc.) . All works of the writer distinguishes subtle psychology and entertaining narrative. Many of the poems AK Tolstoy was set to music by the great Russian composers.
